          • [ - ] RealMadridFan77 - member since 20-Sep-16

            I believe that FC Copenhagen is AT LEAST going to get a point here! I know on paper that Leicester has the strongest squad and the most expensive players, but if you look at the stats for both teams matches vs. Club Brügge and FC Porto, you'll see that Copenhagen actually has the advantage! They had more possession and most importantly of all.. more finishes against their opponents and less finishes towards them, than Leicester have had. Besides that Leicester have gone ALL- IN on the CL and don't look too good in the PL. FC Copenhagen looks VERY strong this season and are in top of the domestic league, which is a feat in itself considering they're playin' in the CL as well! I personally watched FC Copenhagen play against FC Porto in the away game in Portugal. FC Copenhagen had the upper hand and only a red card let FC Porto back in the game! I'm guessing this will be a draw, but if we're going to have a winner, I think FC Copenhagen will surprise everyone and snatch this!
